<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Because Bards don't fit in with hybrids</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Matt">Matt</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:32 p.m. 24/2/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Because Bards don't fit in with hybrids<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1161" TARGET=_self>Why does everyone always forget bards?</A> (Tarwen)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>As far as I can see, there are 5 types of classes in EQ

<P>Fighters-Warriors, Monks, Rogues. Best fighters overall, no magic.
<BR>Hybrids-Shadowknights, Paladins, Rangers. Good fighters with magic. Not as good at fighting as Tanks.
<BR>Bards-A class of their own, they get some decent fighting skills and some unique magical abilities.
<BR>Wisdom-based Casters-Druids, Shamans, Clerics. Bad fighters but still more adept at combat than Int-based casters. The only spellcaster classes that get healing-type spells (unless you count mend bones).
<BR>Intelligence-Based Casters-Wizards, Magicians, Enchanters, Necromancers. Weakest at physical combat out of any class, but with the most devestating magical abilities (IMO).
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
